<subSubSection pageId="183" pageNumber="945" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="183.[1398,2608,288,1151]" pageId="183" pageNumber="945">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1401,1758,997,1030]" pageId="183" pageNumber="945">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Data Deficient on The IUCN Red List. Known specimens of the Diminutive 
<taxonomicName box="[1809,1899,1037,1070]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="183" pageNumber="945" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
came from highly fragmented habitat, and nearby protected areas might not be effective forits long-term survival.
</paragraph>
